Terms of Service for Faceless's Discord Bot/Application

Last Updated: 8th of February 2025

1. Acceptance of Terms
By using "Faceless" (the Bot/Application), you agree to these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, you may not use the Bot.

2. Eligibility
The Bot is hosted on Discord, which requires users to be at least 13 years old. By using the Bot, you confirm that you meet this requirement.

3. Usage Rules
- Users may use the Bot for its intended purposes, such as sending embedded messages and checking statistics.
- Abuse of the Bot, including but not limited to spamming commands, is strictly prohibited.
- Violation of these rules may result in removal from our associated Discord server.

4. Data Collection & Privacy
- The Bot may collect and store data, including but not limited to:
  - Username
  - Display name
  - Profile picture
  - Messages
  - Potentially email (if applicable)
- This data will not be sold but might be shared with third-party companies.

5. Account Management
- Account creation, termination, and suspension are handled exclusively by Discord.
- We do not have control over user accounts and are not responsible for Discord-related issues.
- Users must proceed with caution when using the Bot.

6. Intellectual Property
- All content related to the Bot is owned by us.
- Users may use the Bot but cannot modify or alter it in any way.
- Feature suggestions can be sent via DM to @jaymakesmone (https://twitter.com/jaymakesmone) on X (formerly Twitter).

7. Limitation of Liability
- We strive to ensure the Bot runs smoothly, but we are not responsible for:
  - Service outages
  - Bugs
  - Data loss (though unlikely)
- Use the Bot at your own risk.

8. Enforcement & Server Bans
- While we cannot terminate user access to the Bot directly, we can ban users from our Discord server if they violate our Terms of Service or server rules.

9. Updates to These Terms
- We reserve the right to update these Terms at any time.
- Users can appeal Discord server bans via our Whop Help Desk.

10. Monetization
The Bot is currently free to use.
- In the future, we may introduce paid features or premium plans.

By continuing to use "Faceless" (the Bot/Application), you acknowledge and agree to these Terms of Service. If you have any questions, contact us via X at @jaymakesmone (https://twitter.com/jaymakesmone).

